## What I Learned

* Netstat displays active network connections.
* Listening ports wait for incoming traffic.
* Established connections represent active communication.
* Modern systems maintain many simultaneous network connections.
* Both TCP and UDP are commonly used by Windows systems.
* Netstat can be used to investigate network activity and troubleshoot connectivity issues.

## Cybersecurity Connection

Security analysts frequently use netstat during investigations to identify active network connections, detect suspicious communication, and verify which services are running on a system.

Netstat is often one of the first tools used when investigating potentially compromised systems or unusual network activity.

Understanding active connections helps analysts identify unauthorized communications and investigate security incidents.

